verses.text: Now the serpent was more subtil than any beast of the field which the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God had made. And he said unto the woman , Yea , hath God said , Ye shall not eat of every tree of the garden ?\f + \fr 3.1 \ft Yea…: Heb. Yea, because, etc.\f*
And the woman said unto the serpent , We may eat of the fruit of the trees of the garden :
But of the fruit of the tree which \add is\add* in the midst of the garden , God hath said , Ye shall not eat of it, neither shall ye touch it, lest ye die.
And the serpent said unto the woman , Ye shall not surely die :
For God doth know that in the day ye eat thereof, then your eyes shall be opened , and ye shall be as gods , knowing good and evil. \p

And when the woman saw that the tree \add was\add* good for food , and that it \add was\add* pleasant to the eyes , and a tree to be desired to make \add one\add* wise , she took of the fruit thereof , and did eat , and gave also unto her husband with her; and he did eat.\f + \fr 3.6 \ft pleasant: Heb. a desire\f*

And the eyes of them both were opened , and they knew that they \add were\add* naked ; and they sewed fig leaves together , and made themselves aprons.\f + \fr 3.7 \ft aprons: or, things to gird about\f*

And they heard the voice of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God walking in the garden in the cool of the day : and Adam and his wife hid themselves from the presence of the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God amongst the trees of the garden.  +  r 3.8  t cool: Heb. wind * \p
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God called unto Adam , and said unto him, Where \add art\add* thou ?
And he said , I heard thy voice in the garden , and I was afraid , because I \add was\add* naked ; and I hid myself. \p
And he said , Who told thee that thou \add wast\add* naked ? Hast thou eaten of the tree , whereof I commanded thee that thou shouldest not eat ?
And the man said , The woman whom thou gavest \add to be\add* with me , she gave me of the tree , and I did eat.
And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God said unto the woman , What \add is\add* this \add that\add* thou hast done ? And the woman said , The serpent beguiled me , and I did eat. \p

And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God said unto the serpent , Because thou hast done this, thou \add art\add* cursed above all cattle , and above every beast of the field ; upon thy belly shalt thou go , and dust shalt thou eat all the days of thy life :
And I will put enmity between thee and the woman , and between thy seed and her seed ; it shall bruise thy head , and thou shalt bruise his heel.

Unto the woman he said , I will greatly multiply thy sorrow and thy conception ; in sorrow thou shalt bring forth children ; and thy desire \add shall be\add* to thy husband , and he shall rule over thee.\f + \fr 3.16 \ft to thy…: or, subject to thy husband\f* \p

And unto Adam he said , Because thou hast hearkened unto the voice of thy wife , and hast eaten of the tree , of which I commanded thee , saying , Thou shalt not eat of it: cursed \add is\add* the ground for thy sake; in sorrow shalt thou eat \add of\add* it all the days of thy life ;
Thorns also and thistles shall it bring forth to thee; and thou shalt eat the herb of the field ;\f + \fr 3.18 \ft bring…: Heb. cause to bud\f*
In the sweat of thy face shalt thou eat bread , till thou return unto the ground ; for out of it wast thou taken : for dust thou \add art\add*, and unto dust shalt thou return.
And Adam called his wife’s name Eve ; because she was the mother of all living.\f + \fr 3.20 \ft Eve: Heb. Chavah: that is Living\f*
Unto Adam also and to his wife did the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God make coats of skins , and clothed them. \p

¶ And the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God said , Behold , the man is become as one of us, to know good and evil : and now, lest he put forth his hand , and take also of the tree of life , and eat , and live for ever :
Therefore the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* God sent him forth from the garden of Eden , to till the ground from whence he was taken.
So he drove out the man ; and he placed at the east of the garden of Eden Cherubims , and a flaming sword which turned every way , to keep the way of the tree of life.
